<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><?xml-stylesheet href="\\Ameras0036\Data\BIEM_PRODUCTION_AMERICA\053_NJT\Application\p-xml\XSL\053_NJT_ib.xslt" type="text/xsl"?><!--thru 053_NJT_p-iem_IB.xslt--><ib miid="BOM01312" doc-type="MI" maint-item-desc="Cab Communication Control Panel" part-number="05384180011S" doc-name="BOM01312_MI" doc-title="Cab Communication Control Panel" lock-counter="9" search-index="mim-sys9-dno" show-e-list="yes" e-list-number="09 01 01" giid-maint-item-desc="Cab Communication Control Panel" id-document="26680" id-document-version="41256" doc-version="0" pmt-version="14" gmt-version="12" user-defined-1="" user-defined-2="" user-defined-3="" oem-part-no="" device-name="CCCP"><maintenance-item><para reuse="all">The Cab Communication Control Panel (CCCP) allows
the train operator to operate all train audio communication devices,
including the VHF radio.</para><para reuse="all">The CCCP is located in the cab of the C Car.
(See Figure <ref-container><iref ref-id="BGBGFEEC"></iref></ref-container>.)
The unit is attached to the Cab Car structure, above the train operator console,
left of the windshield. The CCCP unit weighs approximately 12 lb
and measures approximately 13.8 inches high, 6.5 inches
wide, and 5.0 inches deep. The panel face is brushed stainless
steel and the body is aluminum with a chemical conversion coating. </para><illustration reuse="all"><graphic file="..\..\Graphics\CGM\053J-732-001.cgm" cropped="1" float="0" height="5.70in" impsize="9.00in 5.70in"></graphic><title id="BGBGFEEC">Cab Communication Control Panel</title></illustration><para reuse="all">The panel face is engraved with label text permanently
marked in black. The face is pierced to provide protection grills
for a speaker and for an array of three microphones. Various indicators
and controls are also found on the panel face (see Table <ref-container><iref ref-id="BGBDHEDC"></iref></ref-container>). When pressing an operating
mode pushbutton, the button status LED turns on, the associated
mode is selected and activated, and any previously selected mode
is canceled. Audio transmissions are heard through a face-mounted speaker. </para><table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1" reuse="all"><title id="BGBDHEDC">CCCP Controls and Indicators</title><tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="1"><colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="1.125in"></colspec><colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="1.125in"></colspec><colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="4.750in"></colspec><thead><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1">LABEL</entry><entry colname="2">TYPE</entry><entry colname="3">DESCRIPTION</entry></row></thead><tbody><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="left">CHANNEL</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">LED Indicator</entry><entry colname="3" align="left">Radio Channel Indicator</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="left">(None)</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">Rotary Selector</entry><entry colname="3" align="left">Radio Channel Selector<para reuse="all">Controls the radio channel selector.</para></entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="left">VOLUME</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">Rotary Switch</entry><entry colname="3" align="left">Radio Speaker Volume<para reuse="all">Controls radio speaker volume, from 25 to 100
percent.</para></entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="left">PEI CANCEL</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">Pushbutton With Status LED</entry><entry colname="3" align="left"><para reuse="all">Green/amber
status LED</para></entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="left">IC</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">Momentary Pushbutton With Status
LED</entry><entry colname="3" align="left">Intercom Mode<para reuse="all">Green
status LED indicates Intercom (IC) mode is active. </para></entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="left">PEI</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">Momentary Pushbutton With Status
LED</entry><entry colname="3" align="left">Passenger Emergency Intercom
Mode<para reuse="all">Green status LED indicates Passenger Emergency
Intercom (PEI) mode is active. Pressing on PEI button during a call
places that call on hold. </para></entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="left">PA</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">Momentary Pushbutton With Status
LED</entry><entry colname="3" align="left">Public Address Mode<para reuse="all">Green status LED indicates Public Address (PA)
mode is active. </para></entry></row><row rowsep="0"><entry colname="1" align="left">RADIO</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">Pushbutton With Status LED</entry><entry colname="3" align="left">Radio Mode<para reuse="all">Green
status LED indicates radio mode is active. Pressing RADIO initiates
a remote call. </para></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><para reuse="all">Four car wiring cables connect to the CCCP with
10-pin plugs. (See Table <ref-container><iref ref-id="BGBGABAI"></iref></ref-container>.) A ground wire connects
the CCCP to the carbody. </para><table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1" reuse="all"><title id="BGBGABAI">CCCP Connections</title><tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="1"><colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="1.250in"></colspec><colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="1.125in"></colspec><colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="4.250in"></colspec><thead><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1">CONNECTOR ID</entry><entry colname="2">PIN NO.</entry><entry colname="3">DESCRIPTION</entry></row></thead><tbody><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="center">GND</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">-</entry><entry colname="3">Carbody ground</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="center">J1</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">1 - 9</entry><entry colname="3">Radio control lines</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" morerows="3" align="center">J2</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">1,2</entry><entry colname="3">Cab Master Door Control Panel</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="2" align="center">3,4</entry><entry colname="3">Cab makeup relay</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="2" align="center">5,6</entry><entry colname="3">Alerter/Indicator Control Unit</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="2" align="center">9 -10</entry><entry colname="3">Radio microphone</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" morerows="1" align="center">J3</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">1,2</entry><entry colname="3">Power (supplied by CCU)</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="2" align="center">5,6</entry><entry colname="3">Dedicated CCCP audio channel (from CCU)</entry></row><row rowsep="0"><entry colname="1" align="center">J4</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">1 - 8</entry><entry colname="3">RS-485 Audio Control Network (shared by the
CCCP and all CCPs and PEIs)</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></maintenance-item></ib>